course: main course
servings: 2
time required: 20 minutes
---

Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a large #pot of salted @water{to taste}.

Halve the @baby potatoes{500%g} (quarter larger pieces). Roughly chop the @parsley{5%g}.

When the water is boiling, add the potatoes, lower the heat to medium and cook until fork
tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Drain in a #colander and return to the #pot, off the heat. Stir
through a knob of @butter{to taste} along with the parsley. Season to taste with @salt{to taste}
and @pepper{to taste}. Cover to keep warm.

Meanwhile, pat the @hake{250%g} dry with #kitchen paper{}.

Arrange the hake on a lined #baking tray{}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

Spread the @green pesto{1%sachet} evenly over the tops of the hake fillets.

Season the @breadcrumbs{1%pack} with salt and pepper. Spoon equal amounts of the breadcrumbs onto
each fillet. Press down firmly with the back of the #spoon to ensure it adheres.

Place the hake on the top shelf of the oven. Bake until the breadcrumbs are golden and the fish
is cooked through, ~{10-15%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, trim and quarter the @radish{125%g}. Just before serving, toss the radish and
@salad leaves{40%g} with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Divide the pesto crumbed hake fillets between #plates{}, adding a dollop of @mayo{1%sachet} to the
top of each. Serve the radish salad and parsley butter potatoes alongside. Finish the salad
with a drizzle of @balsamic glaze{1%sachet}.